My Christian Mingle Acct. was HACKED on 09/30/21 at 8:13pm. I was fortunate to receive an email that my email was changed within 30minutes of the hack. It advises "We will try our very best to reply to you within the next 48 hours." but it has now been over 48hrs and I've not received any kind of response. The following personal details are now completely accessible to the hacker: Full Name Address Username Email Address Password (that I've spent the past few days changing on my other accts) Credit Card Info All of my personally identifying info that you would list on a dating profile in order to attract a like individual including: College Attended Marital Status, etc. LITERALLY EVERYTHING ONE WOULD NEED TO COMMIT IDENTITY THEFT!!! And I'VE NOT RECEIVED ANY REPLY from this company! You would think there would be some level of urgency for such a situation. When my PROFILE PICTURE WAS REJECTED & I emailed them asking why - CUSTOMER SUPPORT replied in less than 10HRS!!! But here someone has access to COMMIT IDENTITY THEFT and not to mention MESSAGE all of my matches pretending to be me - and I HEAR NOTHING from this company. I'm so insanely disappointed. Now I'm spending the weekend doing damage control on all of my other accounts that have the same email/password combination. What are your hours of operation??? Where are you headquartered? Where is your customer support center? What time zone? My next step is to write the Better Business Bureau.

content: A lot of inconsistencies with the app vs the website.  Search results very incomplete (only 10% of what the site shows show up on the app) vs the app.  This is even with "any" selected for all search criteria, I've checked.  It shows all matches, not just the new ones, so the 5-6 daily new ones get mixed in with all the others you've already seen.  Like others have said, a lot of the info the site shows under the profile pic on all the different "tabs" is not shown, and you have to view the profile to see that info, but this is a more minor point.  Also, you can't view previous activity as far back on the app as you can on the site.  On the plus side, the app allows you to list favorite TV shows, movies, music, etc.  The app also shows how far someone is willing to relocate (or not relocate) when you view their profile.  On the contrary, the website doesn't list this info.  You basically need to use the site and app simultaneously to be able to see all the info available and post as much about yourself as is possible. content: Summary: Not awful, but sub-par with a clunky interface and less than helpful customer service.  I'm still mystified by what algorithm they use (or do not use) to calculate compatibility (OKCupid and eHarmony are light years ahead), and--as a law-abiding and rather circumspect Christian--I found the content moderation policy (i.e.., that admins must separately approve every edit you make to your profile and every photo you post) to be just a little bit insulting (not to mention inefficient!).  I'd give them a 1.5/5.0.  PSA: If you subscribe (and I'd recommend against it), make your first action as a subscriber to turn off auto-renewal.  I received notification that my subscription (which I did not intend to keep) had auto-renewed, immediately  asked Customer Support to cancel my account and refund the money (since I haven't been on the site for at least a couple of weeks and thus the extension was completely unused), and was given a rather curt reply denying the request.  They are arguably within their rights to do so, but the fact that they are so desperate to keep unwilling subscribers should give you some indication about the quality of the service they are selling...
replyContent: Thank you for commenting Jonathan. We would be happy to review your profile with you and assist you with match and search settings to receive the best results. replyContent: Thank you for your comment, Mo.  We are not offering the option to unsubscribe through the app at this time but it's a feature we would like to implement in the future.
